<Window x:Class="SpectatorFootball.Help_Forms.Help_Draft"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:SpectatorFootball.Help_Forms"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Height="250" Width="700" WindowStyle="none" ResizeMode="NoResize" ShowInTaskbar="False" Topmost="True">
    <Border Style="{StaticResource popupBD}" BorderThickness="1">
        <StackPanel Style="{StaticResource popupSP}" Height="240" Width="690" Orientation="Vertical" >
            <Label Style="{StaticResource popupTT}" HorizontalAlignment="Center">Draft Task</Label>
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HelpTB}" Width="670" Height="160" Margin="5,5,5,0" TextWrapping="Wrap">
The draft window allows you to view the initial or yearly draft for your league.
<LineBreak/>  
<LineBreak/>  
From this window you can view your league's draft.  When conductiong your draft, you have the following options:<LineBreak/>
    *   Advance one draft pick by clicking on the Make Next Pick button.<LineBreak/>
    *   Complete the next round in the draft by clicking on the Sim Round button.<LineBreak/>
    *   Completing the whole draft by clicking on the Sim Draft button.<LineBreak/>
<LineBreak/>
<LineBreak/>
You can select the speed at which draft picks will be made using the Speed slider.  Note that you can change the speed slider<LineBreak/> 
even while picks are being made.<LineBreak/>
                
When a pick is made, you will see the pick announced in the announcer box.<LineBreak/>
                
You can also see a draft profile for a player by double-clicking the player in the Draft Pool list.<LineBreak/>                
<LineBreak/>
<LineBreak/>                
            </TextBlock>
            <Button Name="hlp_nl_close" Style="{StaticResource appSubmitStyle}" Click="hlp_nl_close_Click_1" >Close</Button>
        </StackPanel>
    </Border>

</Window>
